abstract: The 2020 Democrats criticized President Trump’s Iran strategy and top candidates notched significant endorsements, with the Iowa caucuses less than a month away.
snippet: The 2020 Democrats criticized President Trump’s Iran strategy and top candidates notched significant endorsements, with the Iowa caucuses less than a month away.

abstract: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
snippet: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Bernie Sanders edged ahead of his Democratic rivals in Iowa, affirming his resurgence less than four weeks before next month’s caucuses, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.

lead_paragraph: J. Charles Jones, a civil rights activist both in Charlotte, N.C., and nationally who helped organize pivotal events and groups in the 1960s, died on Dec. 27 at his home in Charlotte. He was 82.

headline_main: The Week in Tech: New Decade, Same Old Trouble in Washington
headline_print_headline: New Decade, Same Old Trouble in Washington

abstract: Andrea Masenda, who met Kevin Lo when both were working at ESPN, wasn’t sure she was on a first date, or even if she wanted to be. Mr. Lo had no such doubt.
snippet: Andrea Masenda, who met Kevin Lo when both were working at ESPN, wasn’t sure she was on a first date, or even if she wanted to be. Mr. Lo had no such doubt.
lead_paragraph: Andrea Masenda sat across from Kevin Lo at a Chili’s restaurant in Bristol, Conn., wondering all the while if she was on a first date.

abstract: The New York governor commissioned a surreal poster that shows him navigating a “sea of division” and “squalls of hate.”

abstract: The Granite State’s young people, libertarians and independent voters helped power Bernie Sanders to a primary victory in 2016. This time, some of them are eyeing Andrew Yang and Tulsi Gabbard.
snippet: The Granite State’s young people, libertarians and independent voters helped power Bernie Sanders to a primary victory in 2016. This time, some of them are eyeing Andrew Yang and Tulsi Gabbard.
lead_paragraph: PLYMOUTH, N.H. — Tim Smith is 35, relatively young compared with other voters. He calls himself an independent, which is common here in New Hampshire. And he’s uneasy about the political establishment and Democratic Party standard-bearers.
